# Cosmic Ocean: QA & Testing Bible (V1)

*This document is the definitive quality assurance blueprint. No code reaches production without passing the criteria established here.*

---

## 1. Testing Philosophy
*   **Recruiter Experience First:** The path to the resume and project information must never be obstructed by bugs or complex gameplay.
*   **Stability Over Visual Polish:** If an aesthetic feature (e.g., shaders, whale) causes crashes or frame drops, it must be killed via Feature Flags.
*   **Zero-Friction Fallbacks:** All edge cases (missing assets, network drops, bad JSON) must degrade gracefully. White screens are release blockers.

---

## 2. Smoke Test Suite
*Run this suite manually every time the development server starts.*

| ID | Test Case | Expected Result |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| ST-01 | **Application Startup** | Page loads without white-screen hanging. Loading screen appears instantly. |
| ST-02 | **Asset Loading** | `Promise.all()` completes successfully. Loading screen fades out to reveal the Hub Lagoon. |
| ST-03 | **Boat Spawning** | Boat sits exactly at `(0, 0)` on the water plane, facing North-East. |
| ST-04 | **Camera Following** | Camera locks to the boat with a strict `(+10, +10, +10)` offset. |
| ST-05 | **Resume Mode Opening** | Clicking `[View Resume]` instantly halts 3D rendering and reveals the HTML resume. |
| ST-06 | **Resume Mode Closing** | Closing the resume seamlessly resumes the 3D render loop. |
| ST-07 | **Modal Opening** | Sailing into a Project Monolith trigger radius opens the Case Study Modal. |
| ST-08 | **Modal Closing** | Pressing `Esc` or clicking outside the modal closes it and returns focus to the canvas. |
| ST-09 | **Lighthouse Sequence** | Entering the Harbor `(200, 300)` with fragments activates the volumetric light and shows the Contact Form. |
| ST-10 | **Contact Form** | Submitting dummy data results in a success state and fires `contact_submitted` analytics event. |

