## 5. Accessibility Testing
*   **Keyboard Navigation:** Open the site. Do not touch the mouse. Use `Tab` and `Enter` to navigate to `[View Resume]`, tab through every project, and submit the contact form.
*   **Focus States:** Ensure every tabbed element has a visible `2px solid #00F0FF` outline.
*   **Screen Reader Support:** Verify the HTML Resume tree uses proper `<main>`, `<section>`, `<h1>`, and `<h2>` hierarchy.
*   **Reduced Motion:** Toggle OS-level "Reduce Motion." Verify animations freeze and modal transitions become instantaneous.

---

## 6. Performance Testing & Profiling
If any thresholds are breached on target devices, the corresponding Kill Switch must be flipped. Use Chrome DevTools Performance Tab.

### 6.1 Browser Profiling & Logging Requirements
*   **Performance Metrics Logging:** In development mode, the application must log the following metrics every 5 seconds: FPS, Draw Calls, Triangles, Memory Usage, Load Time.
*   **Main Thread Time:** `< 16ms` per frame to ensure solid 60FPS.
*   **Memory Usage Monitoring:** Leave the project running for 30 minutes. Memory growth must stabilize. There must be no increasing heap trend.
*   **Context Loss:** Simulate WebGL context loss. Application should attempt recovery or show error without locking the browser.

### 6.2 Hard Budgets
| Metric | Target | Failure Threshold | Action / Kill Switch |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Target FPS** | 60 FPS | Drops below 45 FPS | Trigger `enablePostProcessing: false` |
| **Draw Calls** | < 80 | > 120 | Merge static meshes. Remove particle wakes. |
| **Triangle Count**| < 100k | > 150k | Switch Ocean to `MeshStandardMaterial`. |
| **Asset Size** | < 10 MB total | > 15 MB | Aggressively Draco-compress remaining GLBs. |

